Let OTTO Plants assist your load bank testing control systems at a leading power factor with this capacitive load bank. Uninterruptible power supplies, computer servers and DC power supplies create leading power factors on their power distribution systems. Leading power factors are a known problem for voltage regulators on emergency diesel generators. If leading power factors are common at your facility, make sure your generator's controllers can operate at the power factor they will see when they are in service. This load bank can also be used to correct power factor at facilities with low-power factors or increase voltage on utility power systems. Let OTTO Plants supply equipment to support your daily work needs. Add capacitance to your power distribution system to test control systems at a leading power factor
Increase voltage on utility power systems
2,000 kVAR capacitance at 480V
1,500 kVAR capacitance at 415V
Uses: Ideal to add capacitance to your power distribution system

Ideal for power quality measurement and commissioning agents (CAs) that need to capture transients during testing UPSs, motor generators, turbines, ATS/STSs, medium voltage, as well as general power quality testing. This testing tool has the ability to capture Delta and Wye AC simultaneously with no preset determination and can also measure DC voltage, DC current (including ripple) for DC bus/jar/cell voltages, and temp/humidity from wireless probes (up to 100 locations) during the same test. The PQM (power quality meter) is sophisticated with customizable features that can examine a minimum of 256 samples per cycle on 5 voltage and current channels triggering off of voltage and current up to a high-frequency examination at 1.666M samples per channel with 12 A/D resolution. The PQM comes with free software to view the data live and write the transient reports. PQM that captures AC or DC voltage, watts, KVA, frequency, V&I, harmonics and THD, KVAR, PF, total KVA, total kW, total KVAR, total kWH
Optional wireless or ethernet connected DC probe that can measure DC voltage, DC current (2,00A or 4,000A options), AC voltage, AC current, watts and voltage, and ripple current
Clamp-on AC current probes are available in 10A and 200A sizes, and flexible Rogowski coils are available in 3,000A and 6,000A sizes in 24”, 36” or 48” diameters
Comes in its own shipping case along with calibration certificates
Optional commissioning and power quality report writing service available
Uses: Ideal for PQM and CAs that need to capture transients during testing UPSs, motor generators, turbines, ATS/STSs, and medium voltage

Centrifugal trash pumps pass foreign material such as stones, leaves, mud and various other solids that can clog other pumps. Should clogging occur, you can easily remove the clean-out cover by loosening the hand knobs; no tools required. Trash pumps pass solids half the size of the suction opening, i.e., a 2" trash pump passes 1" spherical solids. Our pumps also pass up to 25%, by volume, of sand, silt and mud. Units are self-priming, and once you fill the casing with water, you're ready to go. The heavy-duty tubular steel frame increases portability and component protection. 2" suction and discharge ports
Pump will pass 1" solids
Pumps up to 185 gallons per minute (0.7 M3M)
